description:

We've covered the story earlier this year, but it's going national. Andy Henry's family has owned farmland in New Jersey for close to 2000 years. The town is threatening to seize his property to build affordable housing using eminent domain.

Now, we get to here from one of the douchebags making the threat. Meet Committee member Matt Scott. He says he isn't the bad guy and that the Henry Family Farm needs to be seized by the government for the -- wait for it --- "greater good."
title: Democrat official claims he's not the bad guy SEIZING farm family owned for 200 years because it's for the "greater good"
